response: "{ \"title\": \"Medium: Reverse Words in a String\", \"description\": \"Given a string `s` consisting of words separated by spaces, write a function `reverse_words` that reverses the order of the words in the string while preserving the original word order within each individual word.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing words separated by spaces.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the string with the order of words reversed.\\n\", \"code\": \"def reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n    return ' '.join(s.split()[::-1])\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert reverse_words(\\\\\"Hello world\\\\\") == \\\\\"world Hello\\\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\\\"the sky is blue\\\\\") == \\\\\"blue is sky the\\\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\\\"a b c\\\\\") == \\\\\"c b a\\\\\"\"] }"
